  "prompt": "How do you find out the status of an SFSU application?",
  "response": "You can check the status of your SFSU application through the **SFSU Application Portal**. Here's how:\n\n1.  **Go to the SFSU Application Portal:** This is usually the same portal you used to submit your application. Look for a link on the SFSU website (search for \"SFSU Application Portal\" or \"SFSU Admission Status\") or check the email you received when you submitted your application \u2013 it should contain the portal link.\n\n2.  **Log in:** Use the username and password you created when you applied.  If you've forgotten your credentials, there should be a \"Forgot Username\" or \"Forgot Password\" link.\n\n3.  **Check your application status:**  Once logged in, you should be able to see the status of your application. The portal will typically show:\n\n    *   **Application Received:** Indicates that SFSU has received your application.\n    *   **In Review:**  Indicates that your application is being reviewed by the admissions committee.\n    *   **Decision Made:**  Indicates that a decision has been made on your application. You'll likely receive an email notification directing you back to the portal to view the decision.\n    *   **Admitted/Accepted:** Congratulations! You've been accepted to SFSU.\n    *   **Denied/Rejected:** Your application was not accepted.\n\n**Important things to keep in mind:**\n\n*   **Allow Processing Time:**  It takes time to process applications. Don't expect an immediate update. Check the SFSU admissions website for estimated processing timelines.\n*   **Check Regularly:** While SFSU may send emails about important updates, it's a good idea to check the portal regularly.\n*   **Contact Admissions (If Necessary):** If you have questions about your application status or haven't received updates within the expected timeframe, you can contact the SFSU Office of Admissions.  Find their contact information on the SFSU website. Be prepared to provide your application ID or other identifying information.\n*   **Email is Key:** Ensure that the email address you provided on your application is active and that you check your spam/junk folders regularly.  Important communications from SFSU will likely be sent via email.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to easily check the status of your SFSU application. Good luck!\n",
